The spokesman of the House of Representatives, Abdulrazak Namdas, has been turbaned as the Gangwi of Ganye in Ganye Local Government of Adamawa State. Performing the turbaning, the Gangwari of Ganye Alhaji Umaru Adamu Sanda, said Namdas is the first to be bestowed with such traditional title, which means an ambassador of the Ganye people. He said Namdasâ€™ performance as a representative of his people has been blazing, urging him to continue doing the good work he has been doing. Also speaking, Governor Muhammad Jibrilla Bindow of Adamawa State commended Namdas for his style of representation.